This paper is about a deep learning framework for decomposing an image of a human face into shape, reflectance, and illuminance. The paper focuses on computer vision and image processing, which suggests that it is most likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The paper also involves deep learning techniques, which makes it relevant to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves artificial intelligence and image analysis, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also involves graphics and rendering, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.GR (Computer Graphics) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves image and video processing, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category.
